  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_2' aria-label=\" K. Gopi versus The Sub-Registrar & Ors. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('2','2025','2025_5_47_57','2025INSC462'); ><font size='4'> <strong>K. GOPI<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>THE SUB-REGISTRAR & ORS. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 5 S.C.R. 47</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 462</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010001342025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : ABHAY S. OKA<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, UJJAL BHUYAN</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Matter pertains to the correctness of order by the Division Bench of the High Court with regard to upholding the order of the sub-registrar, refusing registration of a sale deed. Headnotes&dagger; Registration Act, 1908 &ndash; s.69 &ndash; Registration (Tamil Nadu r.55A &ndash; Vires of r. 55A &ndash; Refusal of the Sub-registrar to register the sale deed on the ground that the title of the vendor and the appellant not established &ndash; Correctness &ndash; Sub-Registrar refused to register sale deed executed in favour of the appellant &ndash; On<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 06-04-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 3954/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Appeal(s) allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('2','2025','2025_5_47_57','2025INSC462','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-seco